      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Bench-scale hemolysis validation against FDA pump experimental data",
      "description": "CFD-predicted relative hemolysis index compared against FDA generic centrifugal pump experimental measurements across 5 flow-speed operating points. Mean absolute error in RH index was 0.043 (within acceptance threshold of 0.10). Validation was executed under solver configuration ansys-cfx-15-build-2026-q1-build-7-rc2, which preceded the final release build by a single patch revision. The release engineering team confirmed that the only change between rc2 and the final build was a correction to a floating-point rounding routine in the post-processing output formatter; the core solver numerics, turbulence model coefficients, and hemolysis power-law integration kernel were unchanged. On this basis the validation results are considered directly transferable to the released build without re-execution of the full validation suite.",
      "passedCriteria": true,
      "quantitativeOutcome": "Mean |delta RH| = 0.043 across 5 operating points; all within acceptance band RH < 1.0 relative to predicate.",
